Annotation.note:
Find the singular locus of the discriminant of a generic (univariate)
monic polynomial $p(x)$ of degree $n$. The discriminant determines
polynomials with mutliple zeroes and can be computetd as the resultant
$d$ of $p$ and its derivative with respect to $x$.

The singular locus consists of those parameter values where $d$ and
its partial derivatives vanish.

It can be generated by the following code:
\begin{verbatim}
#requires System=Reduce 
 p:=x^n + for i:=0:(n-1) sum mkid(a,i)*x^i;
 d:=resultant(p,df(p,x),x);
 polys:=d . for i:=0:(n-1) collect df(d,mkid(a,i));
 vars:=for i:=0:(n-1) collect mkid(a,i);
\end{verbatim}

\begin{keywords}
Singular Locus
\end{keywords}
